      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Judah went with Simeon — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "According to their promise, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Jdg 1:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and the laws of justice and gratitude: having finished, as far as they were able, the conquest of what belonged to the tribe of Judah, they went to assist the Simeonites to acquire the possession of what was comprehended in their lot. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "The name of the city was called Hormah — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Either the same place, so called ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 21:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; in which case what was there vowed is here executed; or some other place called by the same name upon the like occasion, which seems more probable.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
